Acer Says Security Breach Released Packard Bell Customer Names, Numbers

-- B y   T i m   C u l p a n
-- 
2011-06-10T08:50:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-10/acer-says-security-breach-released-packard-bell-customer-names-numbers.html
Acer Inc. (2353) , the world’s third-largest
computer maker, said a security breach resulted in the release
of customers’ information at its Packard Bell unit.  Name, address, phone, e-mail and product serial numbers
were released, while “no  credit card  or other personal data
appears to have been included,” Acer spokesman Henry Wang said
in an e-mailed response to questions.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tim Culpan in Taipei at 
 tculpan1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Anand Krishnamoorthy at 
 anandk@bloomberg.net  